DevOps Workflow and Toolchain

1. Version Control (Git)
Developers commit code changes to a shared repository using Git.
Tools: Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket.

2. Continuous Integration (CI)
Automatically build, test, and validate code changes.
Detect issues early in the development process.
Tools: Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, Travis CI, CircleCI.

3. Continuous Deployment (CD)
Deploy code to various environments (dev, staging, production).
Automate deployment pipelines.
Tools: Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, Ansible.

4. Security and Compliance
Integrate security checks into the pipeline.
Scan for vulnerabilities.
Tools: SonarQube, OWASP ZAP, Twistlock.

5. Collaboration and Communication
Foster communication between teams.
Tools: Slack, Microsoft Teams, Jira, Confluence.